<font color="#FF0000">LOOKING FOR LOST FRIEND</font><br>
<tt>Sun Apr 13 14:54:09 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
I met James Douglas Davis, Jr.(he went by the name Doug) in Washington, D.C. 1966 while he was in the Marine Corps.  He was stationed in Chu Lai for part of the time he was in the service.  We wrote to each other until he came back to the States sometime in 1968.  He was supposed to write to me when he got home so I would have his address and be able to keep up with each other.  He never wrote and I would sincerely like to hear from him.  I have thought about him often in the last 30 yrs.  He was originally from Greenville, Alabama and I will be in Alabama in July.  He knew me by the names of Kay Vickers and Kay Fink.  If anyone knows where he is or how he is I would love to at least hear about him.
<p><code>-- KH2OSKIER@AOL.COM  (Kay Vickers Corlett) </code><p>


